There are generally four stages to planning and executing a robbery of a retail store:

2. Get access to weapons and disguises: These items will be used in order to scare potential witnesses, and can also come in handy if a fight breaks out.

3. Pick out your date and location: Look for stores that don’t regularly staff an armed officer, as they will have less security. Choose a time when the store won’t be busy, as this will reduce the possibility of witnesses.

4. Execute the plan: On the appointed day, move in as quietly and quickly as possible and take whatever you came for. Leave everything else behind, as the risk of being caught with too much will only cause a lengthy sentence.

Once in the store, the key is to remain calm, focus on your goal, and keep control of the situation by threatening to hurt customers and employees. Leave the building in an orderly fashion, so as not to draw attention. Make sure to double-check the getaway driver has arrived. It is also important to ensure that surveillance tapes and alarms don’t capture your faces or voices. Finally, always remember to clean up after yourselves and leave the store in the same condition as you found it.
